reviews.text: Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.

Had a romantic dinner with my husband here for my birthday. Beautiful restaurant, wonderful staff, delicious food and drinks. Waitress (can’t recall her name, I think it was Jeannine) was knowledgeable, funny, and personal. My husband had the special, it was halibut, which was tasty but very small portioning. My plate had large portions so I guess it depends on what you order. Overall the experience was great!

My friend and I love discovering new places especially when we travel. I found this online before we went to Rome and booked for dinner. We ended up having breakfast twice and lunch twice.. If you love your açai bowls or your smoothies in the morning, this is perfect, if you love pancakes, then this is for you too, of course the menu has more to offer. Here’s just a selection of what we tried. Everyone needs to try this place. Delicious
One of my favorite small downtown restaurants.  Great lunch and dinner.  Unique and flavorful dishes.  Great service and atmosphere.  Parking can be tricky during busy times.

The bartenders here make some rad drinks for sure! I’m not a mixed drink kind of person but that’s all I order at this restaurant. They put on a show and give you some attitude....in a good way! The beef curry is the best I’ve ever had.....Great restaurant!
the service and drinks were exceptional.  but I didnt really like what I ordered. next time I'll get something else. but the dragon drink is amazing!!!

The Fox Theatre is almost legendary for how stunning it is, and it simply cannot be put into words how great this place is to visit. For adults, they offer some alcoholic beverages, but for the children they have popcorn and candy and stuff like that. The views are great from every seat, and the actors they put on are the best in the south. Les Miserables was amazing to witness, and with the great views, nice staff, and plenty of eating options, it's going to be hard to pass in the south. Absolutely recommend to anyone who wants a more formal night on the town with their family, friend, or lover.

The Fox is one of Atlanta's great dames. It's a beautiful palace. Architecturally stunning Moorish style design. Great place to see Broadway shows and attend events in the grand Egyptian ballroom.  But had a blast seeing my girl Mariah Carey! The BEST!

I love the Fox. It is a great music venue. It’s hard to believe that this historic Arabian motif building was almost torn down. The venue has approximately 4,600 seats all with unobstructed views. We just saw Trevor Noah, and we have see other musicals and concerts.
If you’re visiting Atlanta it’s one of the “must see” places here for the history and a great experience. It is a pricey for drinks and refreshments but that’s expected.One of my favorite places in Atlanta.

The beautiful Fox Theater is a landmark  in Atlanta. Wonderfully restored many years ago. I recently saw Les Miserables and sat in the orchestra section toward the back. No problem seeing the stage and all of the actors. The sound was clean and loud enough to be easily heard. If you have never been, please go. The wonderful blue star lit sky inside the theatre is amazing. The only negative is the traffic and parking. Very congested.  Took almost 1 hour to just get out of the parking garage.

This establishment is one of my all time favorite places to be. It definitely is my happy place. I have been to a total of 6 Broadway Productions and they were all so different in style and The Fox theater housed them so well. Very happy to have this Majestic theater in Atlanta.
Great outdoor sitting arrangement. Good food. Cream cheese, honey and fresh fruits make a great dessert. Surely try that one out.
Verdict delicious food. Specially lamb
Just great! Great food, great service!
Best Greek ever!!
Nice atmosphere food and servics
Delightful place,  fresh and yummy cusine. Pot of tea is standard the minute you sit down. One of my happy places.
Nice staff, good food, good prices. Pleasant and quiet most times, even during lunch time.

This place is not good. I ordered chicken and basil, as well as a $10, or more order of vegetables, for a total cost of approx $40 after tax and tip. Nevertheless, I received some chicken bones and fatty tissue, and veggies drowned in sauce. I cannot recommend this place at all.
Fast and delicious. Crab rangoons are hot and tasty!
When they say spicy they mean spicy. The Spicy Szechuan Fish made my eyes water, my nose run. It'll give my dog heartburn if he drinks out of the toilet! But it was wonderful!

Good is fine if you are looking for a quick bite. The place is clean with moder decor.  The food quality is pretty good but the taste is very ordinary.  I usually order Cantonese Fried noodle and steam rice stuffed with shrimp.  The service is extremely quick and dishes are fair size.

The restaurant offers a lot of choices on their menu and you're sure to find something that will interest you. In general the place is clean and seems somewhat new. However the service barely gets a passing grade. Some of them seemed asleep and some of them just seemed disinterested. The food is not bad and not very good either. So everything was pretty average. Except for the portions which are pretty big. You do get your bang for your buck.

It was a great place for a quick bite and so comfy Chinese food.
We walked in around afternoon time and the prices were very reasonable.
Definitely a go to place when in town.

My wife found this busy Chinese restaurant and she also had to wait for a table. We made reservations and when we arrived there were dozens of people waiting. The menu is vast and takes awhile to read with dozens of exotic dishes including some Thai dishes. The servings were quite large so we had plenty to take home. Try the BBQ duck as it was fabulous. And the mango slush was also delicious.
Quick.  Good service.  Good food. Fair price. Big. Clean.  Been going there forever

For just £3 you get to walk round the beautiful grounds of one of Cambridge's college. 

Some great architecture and wonderful greenery, bridges going over the river cam to watch the people punting.

When in the early evening and the colours are just spectacular.
One of the more well-known colleges in Cambridge with a large college ground near the city centre. Look out for the famed Newton's apple tree outside the college too!

Firstly I would like to say that the hospitality I received here would perhaps have been familiar to an Eastern European under a Mongul invasion. The porters hurled racist and sexist abuse to my grandmother and proceeded to give the wrong directions to the chapel. I am utterly disgusted and would not recommend to anyone

Had an old friend over, and it was her first and probably would be her only time ever in Cambridge, and they turned her away from taking a look at the college (quite rudely). My friend is in her 70s. It was classless.
Beautiful buildings and atmosphere
Always enjoy the ice cream here. The texture is more like grandma's homemade vs soft serve. Service is quick and the drive thru helps too! Inside has a nice cafe feel to it.

Fabulous Staff and very clean  food is good. Beware, ice cream can give you brain freeze brrrrr. Small price to pay for very customer oriented staff. 5 stars plus, Karen is outstanding this location is fortunate to have an employee of her caliber these days!
Absolutely love this place always friendly service and you can use your imagination to come up with different shakes because they have so many combination options, I go there all the time.
Best ice craem place around, better then Whitey's by far.
Always a great time. Friendly staff and owner. Have standard flavors and always rotating new or special flavors. Gotta check out the doors!!!

One of the best Italian restaurants in Dublin,  in my opinion, for many years. Recently, the restaurant has been refurbished and is now even cosier and more comfortable than it used to be. Also, the menu is very keenly priced and the early-bird menu is especially good value with the Bellini thrown in at no extra charge. The Italian staff are all totally professional, efficient, friendly and welcoming.

The staff was nice and friendly but the dish I had wasn't that great. The presentation was very good but taste and texture could have been better.

Looking at the other reviews, everyone seems to like so maybe it was just me. I will try something different next time.

For everyone else, go there and make up you own mind.

Visited this restaurant by chance on a quiet weeknight. Service was superb as was the food. Mushroom ravioli was the best we’ve ever had compared to many other similar restaurants (our favourite dish). Reasonable prices for the area with many specials. We will definitely be back!

Excellent food and excellent service, went here for a family get together and went for the set menu. Everyone raved about the starters and main courses. Excellent wine too. Slightly disappointed I didn't get the pizza as it looked amazing going to other tables. I'll definitely be back for the pizza, I might be changing my review to five stars. Keep up the excellent work folks! Viva Italia!

Best Italian restaurant in Dublin. 
Definitely our favourite place to have meals whether it's just a quick lunch or romantic dinner!!!
Highly recommended! 10/10

Great coffee not great music. They used fantastic beans for a lovely coffee, which more than made up for the easy-listening covers of songs that deserved better. My friend liked the music though. Recommended.

Visiting a friend & after marching round The Heath I was treated to a lovely lunch & cuppa there. There was even a celebrity sighting; actor Bryan Brown taking in the world as it passed before his cafe table just outside on the patio.

Excellent pit stop to liven up your walk in Hampstead Heath. Unpretentious, friendly and great value. The best thing about it is the people who work there: always kind, funny and mischievous. Always a pleasure to drop by.
Pleasant cafe at the bottom of the hill. Good place to meet before or after doing some climbs on the bike up.

I have been going to calendar for years and never once have a had a warm welcome or so much as a smile from the staff. Today I was told that I can't sit under the heater because someone else might want to sit there! The main waiter/owner (not sure) seems to have utter contempt for the customers and is very rude and disrespectful! I will not spend another penny in that establishment.
What are the correct hours? I tried visiting twice, two different days a week, and it was closed both times. (I heard it's the best in town, though, so still going to give it 4 stars).

The staff could be a bit more cheerful. The gelato taste was average. Definitely not the best we had tried in Tuscany so far.
Cappuccino was plain.

AMAZING icecream and coffee and super friendly staff. Definitely my favourite icecream in Florence historical centre. My kids also had a jam tart and said it was great. Great experience. Recommended and hope to be back soon! 5🌟

The flavors arent the most creative, but this gelato is the real deal. Due to the simplicity of the flavors it is easy to combine them into your favorite combination. The quality is hard to beat, you can tell they use quality natural ingredients.
Try the 2E wine. Perfect complement to the greatest gelato. Nice people.

The history of this place is unbelievable. I was in complete awe the entire time. The architecture is gorgeous. This was a stop on the freedom trail and I couldn't be happier about it. Everyone is very knowledgeable and I was so pleased with my visit.
Went to Ruth Crisp Steakhouse. With my wife and friends. Everything was great.
So cool!!!!! And the best part were the martinis at Ruth Chris Steak House which is in the lobby of the OLD city hall.
Visited this wonderful historic building ,I was there for dinner at ruth chris's located inside

Visiting Boston is a delight. The red line tour is an excellent way for tourists to get to know history on their own.

Throughout the pavement, a brick line allows visitors to follow a map that guides -self-guided- tours of important historical buildings / monuments.

Here we found the Democratic symbol, the donkey and the explanation of the difference between it and the Republican, the elephant.

Don't miss the opportunity to visit Boston, follow the red line tour and learn about a City filled with history. The building at Boston's Old City Hall is exquisite.
